## David Warner

**David Warner** (born 27 October 1986, in Sydney) is a former Australian international cricketer known for his aggressive left-handed batting and explosive starts in limited-overs cricket.

### 🏏 Career Overview

* **Role:** Opening batter
* **Batting Style:** Left-handed
* **International Debut:** 2009 (T20I vs South Africa national cricket team)
* One of the few players to debut internationally in T20Is before playing First-Class cricket.

### 🌟 Achievements

* Key member of Australia’s squad in the

  * ICC Cricket World Cup (Winner)
  * ICC Cricket World Cup (Winner)
  * ICC T20 World Cup (Winner; Player of the Tournament)

* Scored 8,000+ Test runs and 6,000+ ODI runs.

* Former vice-captain of the Australia national cricket team.

### ⚡ IPL Career

* Played for Sunrisers Hyderabad and led them to the IPL title in 2016.
* Also represented Delhi Capitals in the Indian Premier League.

### 📌 Retirement

* Retired from Test cricket in 2024 and from ODI cricket after the 2023 World Cup.
* Continues to play franchise T20 cricket.

